Multifocal serous cystadenoma of the pancreas. A case report and review of the literature. Serous cystadenoma of the pancreas is usually unifocal multifocal tumors are rare. We report a case of multifocal serous cystadenoma of the pancreas in a 48-yr-old female complaining of general malaise. Serum tumor markers, such as CA 19-9, DUPAN-2, and Span-1, were elevated. Abdominal ultrasound (US) and computed tomography (CT) scans revealed two distinct cystic masses in the head and body of the pancreas, respectively. The patient underwent total pancreatectomy. The resected pancreas contained two discrete cystic masses in the head and body